%N A395727 Decimal expansion of the ratio of the minimum area to the mean area of the orthogonal projection of a regular dodecahedron.
%C A395727 The mean area of the orthogonal projection of a convex body is equal to one-fourth of its surface area.
%C A395727 The ratio of the minimum area to the mean area and the ratio of the maximum area to the mean area, for the dodecahedron and the icoasahedron, were apparently first calculated by the Australian statistician Patrick Alfred Pierce Moran (1917-1988) in 1944.
%C A395727 Mean areas of projection and ratios for the five Platonic solids with unit-length edges:
%C A395727   Platonic solid | mean area     | minimum/mean  | maximum/mean | maximum/minimum
%C A395727   ---------------+---------------+---------------+--------------+----------------
%C A395727   tetrahedron    | A120011       | A157697       | 10 * A020832 | A002193
%C A395727   cube           | A152623       | A010722       | 10 * A020832 | A002194
%C A395727   octahedron     | A010527       | A157697       | 10 * A020832 | A002193
%C A395727   dodecahedron   | A131595 / 4   | this constant | A395728      | A182007
%C A395727   icosahedron    | 100 * A180317 | A395729       | A388812      | A245294
%D A395727 G. Kallianpur, P. R. Krishnaiah, and J. K. Ghosh, Statistics and Probability: Essays in Honor of C. R. Rao, North-Holland Pub. Co., New York, 1982, p. 514.
%D A395727 Luis A. Santaló, Integral Geometry and Geometric Probability, 2nd ed., Cambridge University Press, 2004, p. 218.
%H A395727 U. Betke and P. McMullen, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1112/jlms/s2-27.3.525">Estimating the sizes of convex bodies from projections</a>, Journal of the London Mathematical Society, Vol. s2-27, No. 3 (1983), pp. 525-538.
%H A395727 M. G. Kendall and P. A. P. Moran, <a href="https://archive.org/details/geometricalproba033077mbp/page/n77/mode/1up">Geometrical Probability</a>, Charles Griffin & Co., London, 1962, p. 74.
%H A395727 P. A. P. Moran, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/1969305">Measuring the Surface Area of a Convex Body</a>, Annals of Mathematics, Vol. 45, No. 4 (1944), pp. 793-799.
%H A395727 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 04</a>.
%H A395727 <a href="/index/Do#dodecahedron">Index entries for sequences related to dodecahedron</a>.
%F A395727 Equals (2/3) * tan(3*Pi/10) = (2/3) * sqrt(1 + 2/sqrt(5)) = (2/3) * A019952.
%F A395727 Equals phi / (3*sin(Pi/5)) = A001622 / (3 * A019845).
%F A395727 Equals A395728 / A182007.
